│ edit({"file": "llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp", "old": "  // The ValueOnZero is not the bitwidth. But if the cttz/ctlz (and optional\n  // zext/trunc) have one    │
│ use (ending at the select), the cttz/ctlz result will\n  // not be used if the input is zero. Relax to 'zero is poison' for that case.\n  if (II->hasOneUse() && SelectArg->hasOneUse()   │
│ &&\n      !match(II->getArgOperand(1), m_One()))\n    II->setArgOperand(1, ConstantInt::getTrue(II->getContext()));", "new": "  // The ValueOnZero is not the bitwidth. We cannot safely  │
